Licences to which these Regulations apply

1. (1) The following additional definitions shall apply to this Licence: 

“2RN” means RTÉ Transmission Network DAC (trading as 2rn); 

“Aeronautical Primary Radars” means apparatus (including “Star2000” and 
“TA10” models) providing primary aircraft detection used in airport surveillance 
networks at Dublin, Cork and Shannon airports; 

“Base Station” means Apparatus connected to a backhaul network which 
provides a Radiocommunication Service to Terminal Stations using spectrum in 
the 700 MHz Duplex, 2.1 GHz Band and 2.6 GHz Band; 

“Block Edge Mask” or “BEM” is an emission mask that is defined as a function 
of frequency in relation to a ‘block edge’, the latter being the frequency boundary 

















